The combat was fine. Maybe a little janky at times, given that it's still essentially an indie game, but that's something I've stopped faulting imaginative games over a long time ago. I like how locational damage is impactful and bonking people over the head just right drops them. I like how proper equipment is as impactful as, if not more so than stats and skills. I like how fighting multiple people at ones is always difficult. I like how using sneaky shit or positioning can make a massive difference.

KCD did a good job at making me feel like a young, clueless idiot driving the Medieval equivalent of a tank. I found its setting and characters charming. On the whole, a well executed game that ought to be remembered as one of the best, most original titles of recent years (but suffered a callous character assassination for daring to color outside the lines).
